defined_terms.definition_excerpt:
means the following provided by a charitable organization to a person 62 years of age or older in financial need:
(A) housing, including as an independent living facility, assisted living facility, or nursing facility; and
(B) any service designed to meet the unique needs of a person 62 years of age or older, including:
(i) ministerial services;
(ii) government-sponsored indigent health care;
(iii) social services;
(iv) health services;
(v) educational services; and
(vi) donations to an organization that qualifies for an exemption under Subsection (d)(13) or (19).
